Males of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF3DCEEDFBEBF8ABDF273BBD" authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1044,1140,1914,1940]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="176" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ariasi">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF3DCEEDFBEBF8ABDF273BBD" box="[1044,1140,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">A. ariasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFF3DCEEDFB7DF8A8D8363B94" author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." pageId="176" pageNumber="177" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 13 D–F) resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF3DCEEDFB1EF871DE3F3B94" box="[1249,1388,1952,1978]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="176" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itacolomi">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF3DCEEDFB1EF871DE3F3B94" box="[1249,1388,1952,1978]" italics="true" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">A. itacolomi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF3DCEEDFA81F871D8073BCF" captionStart="FIGURE 153" captionStartId="169.[136,235,1379,1403]" captionTargetBox="[161,1413,198,1341]" captionTargetId="figure-264@169.[151,1436,189,1355]" captionTargetPageId="169" captionText="FIGURE 153. Actinopus itacolomi sp. nov., male: A–C IBSP: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D UFMG 18876: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scales lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597563/files/figure.png" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">Fig. 153</figureCitation>
A–C), 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF3DCEEDFC59F817DF173BCE" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1842" box="[934,1092,1990,2016]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="176" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipalpis">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF3DCEEDFC59F817DF173BCE" box="[934,1092,1990,2016]" italics="true" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">A. longipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF3DCEEDFBABF817DFE03BCF" box="[1108,1203,1990,2017]" captionStart="FIGURE 156" captionStartId="172.[136,235,1679,1703]" captionTargetBox="[188,1382,198,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-114@172.[151,1435,189,1655]" captionTargetPageId="172" captionText="FIGURE 156. Actinopus longipalpis C. L. Koch, 1842, holotype, male: A–E ZMB 2107: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc- Prolateral Accessory keel; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel. D. Rastellum, dorsal; E. Rastellum, ventral. Scales lines: A–C: 1 mm; D–E: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597571" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597571/files/figure.png" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">Fig. 156</figureCitation>
A–C), 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF3DCEEDFAFAF817DEF83BCE" authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1285,1451,1990,2016]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="176" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordobensis">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF3DCEEDFAFAF817DEF83BCE" box="[1285,1451,1990,2016]" italics="true" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">A. cordobensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFF3DCEEDFCCEF83DDFFF3428" author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." box="[817,1196,2028,2054]" pageId="176" pageNumber="177" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 15 D–F) and 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF3DCEEDFA6CF83DD83E3402" authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="176" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coylei">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF3DCEEDFA6CF83DD83E3402" italics="true" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">A. coylei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFF3DCEEDFC83F7C3DFBA3402" author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." box="[892,1257,2066,2092]" pageId="176" pageNumber="177" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 16 D–F), by the PA continuous to PAc. They differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF3CCEECFD0DFF4EDBA13CF3" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itacolomi">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF3CCEECFD0DFF4EDBA13CF3" italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">A. itacolomi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF3CCEECFEFFFF12DA9C3CF3" box="[256,463,195,221]" italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF3CCEECFEFFFF12DACE3CF3" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1842" box="[256,413,195,221]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipalpis">A. longipalpis</taxonomicName>
and
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF3CCEECFDF9FF12D9DD3CF3" box="[518,654,195,221]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pindapoy">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF3CCEECFDF9FF12D9DD3CF3" box="[518,654,195,221]" italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">A. pindapoy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by slender bulb and from those of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF3CCEECFE77FF39D9783D2C" authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[392,555,232,258]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordobensis">
